<br>
The Kromrif scout grumbled as he made his way back to Kael Drakkel, limping and bleeding.  Far too many outlanders of late have been seen in the area and working with the Coldain.  And the fact that he had been bested by one would not be viewed favorably by Sergeant Tellsren.<br>
<br>
  &quot;Kromrif.  I want a few words with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
  &quot;Eh?&quot;  The giant turned around and looked down to see a small framed creature hidden beneath a hooded travel cloak and his brow furrowed.  Another outlander.  The person was armed with a stave of some sort, he couldn't quite make out the details.  His first thought was to step on the person and move on, hoping this one's death would salvage his reputation somewhat after his defeat at the hands of the Feir`Dal.<br>
<br>
  &quot;The ranger you fought earlier.  Her blood is still on your weapon, no?&quot;  <br>
<br>
The giant glanced down at the dagger in his hand.  The blood was slowly drying on the velium blade.<br>
<br>
  &quot;Yes.  What of it?&quot;  The giant rumbled, tightening the grip on the hilt in anticipation of challenge.<br>
<br>
  &quot;I require that elf's blood.&quot;  The speaker spoke quietly.<br>
<br>
  &quot;Then get it from her yourself, Outlander.&quot;  The Kromrif sneered.<br>
<br>
  &quot;I do not have the time for such menial activities.&quot;  <br>
<br>
  &quot;You mean you lack the ability to get it from her.  Begone, before I crush your bones to dust.  You've wasted enough of my time.&quot;   The frost giant turned and headed down the ramp to Kael, ignoring the arcane syllables carried on the wind when suddenly he stopped.<br>
<br>
  &quot;On second thought ... here.&quot;  The Kromrif scout handed the dagger to the stranger. <br>
<br>
  &quot;Bel' la dos.&quot;  A faint note of ironic humor laced the speaker's tone as she whispered an arcane phrase and vanished from sight.<br>
<br>
